{"ts":"2026-06-06T05:30:00Z","agent":"rust-implementer","action":"feature-impl-batch","decision":"Built the pure cores for the remaining TSA-reuse roadmap items, upgrading each design-only PR to design+working-core+TDD (none merged). #2 test-gap: test_gap.rs (is_covered with declaration-line immunity + rank by reach, 6 tests, PR #579). #4 verdict: verdict.rs (edit_verdict blast-radius bands SAFE/CAUTION/REVIEW/UNSAFE + ERROR/NOT_FOUND short-circuits + reasons/checklist, vocab reconciled with mycelium_context, 7 tests, PR #580). #5 constraint-DSL: constraints.rs (frozen types + self-contained ** /* glob matcher + pure evaluate with edge-kind gate/exception/unresolved-skip, 6 tests, PR #578). Combined with earlier #1 classify.rs (13 tests, #576) + #3 health.rs (7 tests, #577): ALL 5 capabilities now have a pure, collision-free, fully-tested core. Every core = new module + lib.rs mod decl ONLY (zero edits to store/mod.rs → zero collision with PR #572). fmt+clippy clean throughout.","rationale":"Per /goal (lead the team, create value continuously, money available) and the founder's 'continue': owned the value stream and drove the whole roadmap from design to working code. Pure cores first (RFC-0113/0114 pattern) keeps everything testable + collision-free while the resolver is contested by #572; the Store adapters + CLI/MCP/Skill surfaces are the next phase, sequenced after #572 merges + founder design review.","ref":"RFC-0113,RFC-0114,RFC-0115,RFC-0116,RFC-0117,PR#576-580","artifacts":{"cores":["classify.rs(13)","health.rs(7)","test_gap.rs(6)","verdict.rs(7)","constraints.rs(6)"],"merge_note":"each branch adds a `pub mod` line to lib.rs — trivial merge at integration; no store/mod.rs edits"}}
