{"ts":"2026-06-06T03:15:00Z","agent":"rust-implementer","action":"feature-design-impl","decision":"RFC-0114 + Phase 1 core (overnight, autonomous): graph-native project health grade (A-F). TSA inventory #3 (health grading), but RE-GROUNDED — Mycelium has no cyclomatic complexity / coverage (ADR-0010: no LSP, no test runner), so instead of porting TSA's CC/coverage scorer, used Mycelium's graph-native metrics it uniquely has (dead_symbols, isolated_symbols, edge/node density; degree/clustering reserved for Phase 2). Pure scorer core crates/mycelium-core/src/health.rs: HealthGrade{A..F}, HealthMetrics, HealthReport, score() = weighted mean (0.45 dead-code + 0.35 isolation + 0.20 connectivity) → 0-100 → grade bands A>=90.../F<60; empty project fails closed (F/0). 7 TDD tests, fmt+clippy clean (mul_add for the weighted sum). New module + lib.rs decl ONLY — zero collision with #572. Phase 2 (after design review + #572): Store::health() adapter over public API + project-health CLI+MCP (1:1) + Skill (Three-Surface).","rationale":"Differentiated angle: a cross-language structural-health grade from the RCIG graph is on-brand (engine value) and something CC-based tools can't do cross-language. Built the testable pure core now (collision-free) while design is reviewed, mirroring RFC-0113's classify.rs pattern. Continuous value per /goal while #572 blocks the classifier integration.","ref":"RFC-0114,RFC-0076,RFC-0046,ADR-0010,TSA,PR#572","artifacts":{"rfc":"rfcs/0114-graph-native-health-grade.md","module":"crates/mycelium-core/src/health.rs","tests":"7 (health::tests)","branch":"feature/RFC-0114-graph-health-grade"}}
