{"ts":"2026-06-06T00:30:00Z","agent":"rust-implementer","action":"feature-design","decision":"RFC-0113 (design): stdlib/builtin callee classification tier — the #1 TSA-reuse opportunity. After founder pointed at tree-sitter-analyzer ('参考我的tree-sitter-analyzer项目应该可以留用'), the deep-dive ranked this top: TSA's synapse_resolver/_constants.py (_FALLBACK_STDLIB + builtin/external tables) + __init__.py cascade lift callee classification 83.9%→95.9% with ZERO LSP. Mycelium already has the precise project-resolution tiers (RFC-0092/0103); this RFC adds the final two tiers (import-gated stdlib/builtin/external allowlist → unknown), rescuing the unknown callee tail that inflates dead-code false positives and truncates call graphs. Reuse mode: port-concept (Rust cascade) + copy-data (the frozen tables as per-language PACK DATA, respecting Charter §4 ≤3-file rule). Surfaced as an additive `class` field on existing get-callees/get-dead-symbols output — NO new tool, Three-Surface clean. ADR-0010 compliant (static tables = the sanctioned no-LSP precision lever; SCIP remains the reserved full-type-precision path).","rationale":"Highest precision/effort ratio of the TSA inventory, directly extends just-shipped RFC-0103, zero ADR-0010 risk, non-colliding with the parallel PM (engine domain, not CI/release). Written while the v0.3.0 release re-run finished in the background — value created continuously per the /goal.","ref":"RFC-0113,RFC-0103,RFC-0092,ADR-0010,Charter§4,Charter§5.13,TSA","artifacts":{"rfc":"rfcs/0113-stdlib-callee-classification.md","reuse_source":"TSA synapse_resolver/{_constants.py,__init__.py}","branch":"feature/RFC-0113-stdlib-callee-classification"}}
