{"ts":"2026-06-06T06:30:00Z","agent":"frontend-developer","action":"feature-impl","decision":"Built the IDE plugin Phase 1 MVP (RFC-0112) — editors/vscode/, a VS Code extension that is a THIN CLIENT over the published @aimasteracc/mycelium-sdk@0.3.0 (no Rust toolchain; dogfoods our own shipped SDK). Commands: copyContextForAI (HEADLINE — cursor/selection → context() → clipboard, the embeddable-context-layer differentiator at point of use), findCallers/findCallees, symbolInfo, index. Right-click menu for the headline + callers. Resolves the binary via the SDK or mycelium.binaryPath setting. NOT a language server (ADR-0010). Verified: npm install + tsc --noEmit clean against the REAL SDK types + @types/vscode; full tsc build emits engine.js+extension.js. Zero collision (new editors/vscode/ dir, no engine code touched). RFC-0112 is merged on develop = founder-blessed design.","rationale":"Per founder 'don't pause, create value continuously, money plentiful, time scarce': picked the highest-leverage NON-gated opportunity — opening the editor as a new GTM surface where developers live, founder-blessed (RFC-0112 merged), fully isolated (zero risk to engine/parity), and it dogfoods the v0.3.0 Node SDK we just shipped. Verifiable autonomously via tsc/build even without a VS Code host.","ref":"RFC-0112,RFC-0111,ADR-0010,@aimasteracc/mycelium-sdk@0.3.0","artifacts":{"dir":"editors/vscode/","headline":"mycelium.copyContextForAI","verified":"npm install + tsc --noEmit + build all clean","branch":"feature/RFC-0112-vscode-mvp"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-06T07:00:00Z","agent":"devops-automator","action":"feature-impl","decision":"Built a Mycelium GitHub Action (integrations/github-action/) — a new CI/CD distribution surface. Composite action installs the published @aimasteracc/mycelium CLI (no Rust toolchain), indexes the repo, runs server-status/get-dead-symbols/get-isolated-symbols/get-entry-points, and posts a structural code-intelligence summary to the job summary + (optionally) a sticky PR comment. summarize.py: pure, defensive Markdown formatter (degrades missing fields to em-dash, never fails the job), 4 unittest tests. Verified end-to-end with the real 0.3.0 binary: 4 nodes/4 edges/2 dead/1 isolated/2 entry on a fixture → correct Markdown. Isolated (new dir), dogfoods the shipped CLI, gets richer as health/constraint/test-gap features land (slot in without a workflow change).","rationale":"Founder: don't pause, create value+opportunities continuously, money plentiful, time scarce. Opened the CI/CD surface (a new GTM channel) — the cheapest way for teams to adopt Mycelium is a one-line workflow. Verifiable autonomously (YAML lint + formatter tests + real-binary smoke).","ref":"RFC-0110,@aimasteracc/mycelium","artifacts":{"dir":"integrations/github-action/","files":["action.yml","summarize.py","test_summarize.py","README.md"],"verified":"yaml + 4 tests + real-binary end-to-end smoke","branch":"feature/github-action-code-intel"}}
