{"ts":"2026-06-06T00:01:00Z","agent":"security","decision":"Patched both published RFC-0111 SDKs (Node + Python): reject leading-'-' bare positionals (argv smuggling — CLI would re-parse as a flag), and add a 64 MiB streaming output cap to the Python runner mirroring Node's execFile maxBuffer (subprocess.run buffers unbounded). PR #590.","rationale":"execFile/subprocess avoid the shell so no injection, but a user query of '--root' still smuggles a flag; '--' separator unusable because our flags follow positionals. Unbounded Python stdout can OOM the host. Both are public, shipped surfaces — warrant a security patch.","ref":"RFC-0111 / PR #590"}
