{"ts":"2026-06-06T19:45:00Z","agent":"orchestrator","action":"pm-dispatch","decision":"PM dispatch v94 (2026-06-06): (1) Pre-flight complete: CHARTER §2/§5.1/§5.10/§5.12/§5.13, _orchestrator.md, decisions tail-20, anti-patterns, PM state v93 (9db82ba), v0.2 PRD. (2) Assessed 2 open PRs: #568 (v0.3.0 ceremony, founder-gated, all registries published); PR #626 just opened this dispatch. 0 open P0/P1 issues. Develop CI HEAD 9db82ba GREEN. (3) Implemented RFC-0119 Phase 2: rewrote seed_entry_points — BTreeMap dedup (replaces O(n²) Vec loop), real_in_degree helper (excludes NodeKind::Unresolved stub callers), exact_match merge semantics (AC-4b), rank_entry_points call for importance ordering. 3 RED-first tests: seed_dedup_merges_later_exact_match (AC-4b), context_indexing_query_ranks_subsystem_over_test_fixture (AC-10), stub_callers_do_not_inflate_importance (AC-11). TDD RED→GREEN confirmed. fmt+clippy -D warnings clean. (4) CHANGELOG updated, RFC-0119 ACs 4b/10/11/14-16/18 checked; AC-12/AC-13 deferred to e2e-runner. (5) PR #626 opened (feat(context): RFC-0119 Phase 2). (6) PM state v94 written; decisions.jsonl appended.","rationale":"RFC-0119 Phase 2 is the natural successor to Phase 1 (pure ranking core, now on develop as 5c8e9b9). Phase 2 is the Store adapter that makes the ranking visible to consumers. The BTreeMap dedup correctly handles multi-candidate search (the O(n²) Vec::contains loop was a latent correctness issue for large stores). real_in_degree excludes Unresolved stubs introduced by RFC-0118 Part A so callee counts reflect real graph topology. Test design is intentionally adversarial: alphabetical order would fail AC-4b (aaa < bbb), test-file path prefix would fail AC-10 (crates/ < src/), and insertion order would fail AC-11 (util before process). All three RED-first.","ref":"PR#626,PR#625,RFC-0119,Issue#613,Charter§5.1","artifacts":{"pr_opened":"626 (feat(context): RFC-0119 Phase 2 importance-weighted entry-point adapter)","pr_merged":"625 (chore/pm-state-v93, squash 9db82ba)","rfc_0119_ac_checked":"AC-4b, AC-10, AC-11, AC-14, AC-15, AC-16, AC-18","rfc_0119_ac_deferred":"AC-12 (real-corpus), AC-13 (dogfood transcript) → e2e-runner after #626 merges","pm_state":"v94","escalations":["founder: PR #568 v0.3.0 finalize workflow_dispatch","founder: admin-merge PR #626 once CI green + Codex clean"],"next_p1":"RFC-0119 Phase 3 or RFC-0120 Phase 1 (after #626 merges)"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-06T21:15:00Z","agent":"orchestrator","action":"pm-dispatch","decision":"PM dispatch v95 (2026-06-06): (1) Pre-flight complete: CHARTER §2/§5.1/§5.10/§5.12/§5.13, _orchestrator.md, decisions tail-20, anti-patterns, PM state v94 (2f8857d develop HEAD), v0.2 PRD. (2) Assessed: PR #626 CI RED (docs/rustdoc job: `cargo doc` fails with RUSTDOCFLAGS=-D rustdoc::broken-intra-doc-links — NodeKind not imported in context/mod.rs scope, so [`NodeKind::Unresolved`] intra-doc links broken); PR #627 CI ✅ 22/22 (Codex P1 phantom SHA `1327e600` — not in repo; CI dco-check passed on actual HEAD `6b47402`); PR #568 founder-gated. (3) Fixed PR #626 CI: replaced [`NodeKind::Unresolved`] with [`crate::types::NodeKind::Unresolved`] in seed_entry_points + real_in_degree docs. Commit da552d8 pushed. Codex P2 (window completeness beyond per-candidate window) rejected with justification — out of RFC-0119 Phase 2 scope, deferred to Phase 3. (4) Handled PR #627 Codex P1: rejected with justification (phantom SHA, CI DCO ✅). Admin-merged PR #627 (squash 2f8857d). (5) PM state v95 written. decisions.jsonl appended.","rationale":"RUSTDOCFLAGS=-D rustdoc::broken-intra-doc-links causes intra-doc link resolution errors to be fatal. NodeKind was not imported in context/mod.rs (only EdgeKind+NodeId); the doc comments used bare [NodeKind::Unresolved] which rustdoc could not resolve. Fully-qualified crate::types::NodeKind::Unresolved resolves from the crate root without an import. All other CI jobs (tests, clippy, fmt, coverage, build) were GREEN — the code itself is correct. Codex P1 on #627 was a known false-positive pattern (phantom SHA after rebased branch) handled identically to prior dispatches v85/v88/v89. Merger of #627 unblocks develop from PM state lag.","ref":"PR#626,PR#627,PR#568,RFC-0119,Charter§5.12","artifacts":{"fix_commit":"da552d8 (PR#626 rustdoc NodeKind fully-qualified path)","prs_merged":["627 (chore/pm-state-v94, squash 2f8857d)"],"codex_rejected":["626 P2 (window completeness)","627 P1 (phantom SHA DCO)"],"pr_pending":"626 (CI re-running on da552d8)","pm_state":"v95","escalations":["founder: PR #568 v0.3.0 finalize workflow_dispatch","founder: admin-merge PR #626 once CI green on fix da552d8"]}}
